data.title: Hewitt hoping to take a leaf out of Federer’s book

data.text:
ROGER FEDERER sneaked in for a hit at Tony Roche’s home in the Sydney suburbs before flying to Melbourne for a spot of book-signing yesterday. The Wimbledon champion has not been lured into the biography business; he was dishing out copies of the yearly guide to tennis in which it will be difficult to turn a glossy page without finding mention of him.

Fresh from his fourteenth consecutive victory in a tour event final in Doha over the weekend — his 44th victory in 46 matches — the 23-year-old world No 1 wanted a bit of tweaking on his game, something that Roche, his coaching consultant, who, strangely, never reached an Australian Open final, will be doing as often as is required this year.
